Route to Biodiversity¶

Route to Biodiversity creates awareness about the biodiversity existing along athletic routes, by emphasizing the interconnectedness of human activity and local ecosystems.

  1. Strava: Users provide their Strava activity as the initial input. This activity sets the geographic parameters for our analysis.
  2. iNaturalist: Leveraging the iNaturalist database, we retrieve data about species that have been observed within the vicinity of the provided activity.

The tool then presents the top 10 species most frequently observed in the delineated area. Additionally, users have the option to delve deeper into specific species data, accessing detailed information about their distribution, seasonality, and conservation status, among others.

Route to Biodiversity connects athletic endeavors with ecological knowledge. It enlightens users about the abundant biodiversity along their recreational paths, promoting awareness and advocating for harmonious coexistence with nature.
